2 _TEXT 20190420HAv- Bradford Era  Tuesday, February 3, 1942, Bradford, Pennsylvania obit: Daniel Baker  Roulette    ____    A prayer service for Daniel Baker, 72, of Buffalo, NY, a former Roulette resident, was held Wednesday at the John Lyman Cemetery h
3 CONC ere.  A previous service was held at the home in Buffalo.  The Rev H. Henry Walker of the Roulette Methodist church officiated at the committal service.    Mr. Baker was the eldest son of the late Mr and Mrs A. Baker of Roulette and spent his yout
3 CONC h in Roulette and vicinity.  After serving as deputy sheriff of Potter county for several years, he left here about 30 years ago and went to Niagara Falls, where he served on the police force for several years.    Later moving to Buffalo, Mr. Bake
3 CONC r was employed by the du Pont firm.  He retired two years ago due to ill health.    Survivors include his wife and one son, Harold Baker of Niagara Falls, and a sister, Mrs. Emma Jackson of New York city.  beyondDNA beyondDNA originally shared th
